<item>
            <title>[SPARK-24137] [K8s] Mount temporary directories in emptydir volumes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-24137</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the Spark local directories do not get any volumes and volume mounts, which means we&apos;re writing Spark shuffle and cache contents to the file system mounted by Docker. This can be terribly inefficient.&#160;We should use emptydir volumes for these directories instead for significant performance improvements.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
